 succeeded in 0ms:
# Implementation Review: EDEN Phase 3 — Round 2 update

## Round 1 feedback addressed

### Bug: URI "has a scheme" check not RFC 3986

**Addressed.** Replaced the `urlparse`-based check in `_common.py` and
in `conftest.py` with `rfc3986_validator.validate_rfc3986(v, rule="URI")`
— the canonical JSON Schema URI format validator. Added
`rfc3986-validator>=0.1.1` as a runtime dependency of `eden-contracts`
so the model-side check uses the same implementation as the
parity-side `FormatChecker`.

Spot-checked the validator directly:

```text
'http://exa mple.com/path'  -> None (rejected)
'http://example.com/bad%ZZ' -> None (rejected)
'http://example.com'        -> match  (accepted)
's3://bucket/path'          -> match  (accepted)
'file:///tmp/x'             -> match  (accepted)
'just a string'             -> None (rejected)
```

New reject cases:

- `proposal::artifacts_uri_space_in_host` — `http://exa mple.com/path`
- `proposal::artifacts_uri_bad_percent_encoding` — `http://example.com/bad%ZZ`
- `trial::artifacts_uri_space_in_host`

All 78 tests pass.

## Format coverage check

Only `date-time` and `uri` formats appear anywhere in the six schemas
(grep-verified). Both are now enforced on both sides — in-process by
`rfc3986_validator` + `datetime.fromisoformat`, and via the custom
`FormatChecker` on the `jsonschema` validator.

## Gate status after round 2

- `uv run ruff check .` — pass
- `uv run pyright` — 0 errors, 0 warnings
- `uv run pytest -q` — 78 passed
- `markdownlint-cli2 ...` — 0 errors across 20 files
- `check-jsonschema --check-metaschema ...` — ok

## Review Status

Round 2 — please re-verify the URI fidelity fix and let me know if
anything else is blocking.

